&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced plaster Technician/ Orthopaedic practitioner who holds British Orthopaedic association registration to join our busy but friendly Orthopaedic department teams at London Northwest University Healthcare trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will require you work across three of our Hospital sites which are Northwick Park / Ealing and Central Middlesex hospital sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each of the plaster rooms are based in the Outpatient departments of the Hospitals and provide services to our extremely busy fracture/ virtual fracture and elective Orthopaedic clinics .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently work closely with our Fracture Liaison service colleagues and we also provide a service to our inpatients on our Hospital wards as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So if you have excellent clinical skills and you are committed to providing excellent standards of care as well as promoting positive patient experiences we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Doracia Ollivierre,Outpatient Sister Email address   doraciaollivierre@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
